title: For Sale/Trade:  "Last Ditch" Arisaka
postcontent:
I have two of these so I will let this one go if someone needs one for their WWII collection. It's a Japanese model 99 "Last Ditch" Arisaka. It's in great shape for what it is. What looks like a crack in the stock is the way it's built. They used scraps for the lower part of the stock because of the wood shortage at the end of the war. This gun does seem to be all original and complete as a WWII "LAST DITCH" Japanese Arisaka. It seems to be shootable (Good bore with rifling and a tight bolt fit) but it's been a wall hanger for me. I'm not sure I would want to shoot any of the Japanese "Last Ditch" weapons. 
These are selling for an average of about $250 (please research), but I will let this one go for $150 for a collector (which is less than I paid for it.). Located in Conway.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Nighthawk Recon Enforcer w/ 5 mags, holsters, & case
postcontent:
I am selling my Nighthawk BAPD SOT Enforcer.  This is from their early days when they had the Custom and Tactical divisions.  This 45 ACP pistol was commissioned by the Broken Arrow Police Department Special Operations Team.  There were only 15  pistols commissioned and built to their specs. These pistols were held to very tight accuracy and precision tolerances, like all Nighthawks, but with Nighthawk knowing these were intended to be used in the line of duty.   These came with a Heinie Rear Sight, Trijicon Front Sight, STI Tactical Railed Frame, 5" Bull Barrel, one piece guide rod, Beveled Magazine Well, NIghthawk/VZ Gator Back Grips, and Special Serial number.  The slide and frame were matched and finished by Nighthawk and were engrave under the slide by them as seen in the pics.  In total there were only 15 of these ever made and this is number 2.   Eventually, politics got in the way and these were never received by them do to the city council not giving them funding since these were not approved by them.   As shown in the pics, there is wear by the front from holstering, by the rail from removing a light, left Thumb Safety, and a previous owner is guilty of the idiot mark for reinstalling the slide stop.  
This comes with the 
Nighthawk BAPD SOT Enforcer
1 Nighthawk 8 round Magazine
1 New MecGar 8 round Magazine
3 New Wilson Combat 10 round Magazines
1 New Garret Industries Silent Thunder STX Champion Holster 
1 Blackhawk dual magazine holster

If unable to meet FTF I will ship for the buyer. I also have 700+rounds of 230gr Winchester and some Remington FMJ ammo and 80 rounds mixed of 230gr Hydrashocks and Golden Sabers for carry. This setup is redding to go for carry and competition shooting

I'm selling my Smith and Wesson M&P22. It's the popular 22lr hand gun that is used for training off the M&P line (M&P9/M&P40). It's the fullsize model with the 4.1" barrel. I ended up buying an extra magazine for it. I have really enjoyed it but have found I haven't taken it out in a long time. I bought it as a less expensive way to become familiar with the M&P line but found it is absolutely amazing for introducing new shooters to the hobby. Very fun, very accurate and best of all you can shoot until you are tired and bored and not break the bank.
